{{Noticebox/Official}}


'''Earmuff Mode''', or "Earmuffs" is a feature, that allows a user to reduce the volume of other users outside a customizable radius around them. Earmuffs can be accessed by the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]] through the ''Audio tab'', or in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Settings|Settings]] tab of the [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]], under ''Audio & Voice''. 
While Earmuff Mode is enabled, other users can see if another user has it enabled by looking for an Earmuff indicator at the top right of their [[Special:MyLanguage/Nameplates|nameplate]], as seen below:
[[File:EarmuffPlateScreenshot.webp|alt=Screenshot of a VRChat user's nameplate, the screenshot points out the earmuff icon on the top right of the nameplate.|none|thumb|An earmuff indicator appearing on a nameplate, when active.]]

==Overview==
[[File:Icons Earmuff.webp|thumb|120x120px|Earmuff Icon as it appears in VRChat.]] Earmuff Mode was released as an accessibility feature to the platform, initially in an [[Open Beta]] period on August 5<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-5-august-2022 'Developer Update - 5 August 2022'] on ''ask.vrchat.com''; retrieved September 9, 2025.</ref>, 2022, and then officially launched on August 30<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-30-august-2022 'Developer Update - 30 August 2022'] on ''ask.vrchat.com''; retrieved September 9, 2025.</ref>, 2022. There are different settings and preferences to change how Earmuff Mode is used. The shortcut for quickly toggling on and off Earmuff Mode, is by double-clicking the Audio tab on the Quick Menu. 

==Settings==
Earmuffs Mode can be toggled on or off and comes with different settings, to allow you to customize your preferred way of "muffling" users.

''See also: Earmuff Mode [[Special:MyLanguage/Settings#Earmuff Mode|Settings]] for a streamlined view.''

===Distance===
* This changes the range in meters at which the volume of other players will begin to be reduced.
* Distance value can be set between 0.0-10.0m.

[[File:Earmuff.webp|thumb|A demonstration of the Earmuff Mode menu, and the visual aid indicated by the red and gray circles.]]
===Falloff Distance===
* The falloff in meters of which user volumes will be reduced outside the initial range.
* Falloff distance value can be set between 0.0-10.0m.

===Outside Volume===
* The lowest range a user's volume will be reduced to.
* Outside volume value can be set between 0-100%.

===Always Show Visual Aide ===
* Will toggle the visualization of the Earmuff range to always be visible.
* Toggles between Off/On.

===Include Avatar Audio===
* Whether or not Avatar Audio is affected by Earmuff Mode.
* Toggles between Off/On.

===Forward Cone===
* Adjusts the range to a cone to favor users in front of the user.
* Forward cone value can be set between 0-100%.

===Falloff Forward Shift===
* Adjust the amount of forward offset that the directionality property applies to your Earmuff's falloff zone.
* Forward cone value can be set between 0-100%.

===Shape Follows Rotation of...===
* Whether the shape of the Earmuff cone follows the user's camera (current view) or the root of their avatar. 
* Toggles between Camera and Avatar. 

===Lock Shape Rotation===
* Locks the shape rotation in its current position.
* Toggles between Off/On.

